The following thirdparty solutions are used.
Check out the links below for further information.

The downloads.tar.gz contain versions of all the thirdparty codes.
If you don't wish to download, simply run:
	# TODO: update downloads.tar.gz with noma-ocl and dependencies
	tar -xzf downloads.tar.gz
	./build.sh

To automatically download and build everything simply run "download.sh"
followed by "build.sh". See the scripts for details.

HAM: 
	https://github.com/noma/ham

noma-ocl:
	https://github.com/noma/ocl

Vc: 
	http://code.compeng.uni-frankfurt.de/projects/vc/
	NOTE: MIC support is in the master branch of git://code.compeng.uni-frankfurt.de/vc.git

VCL (Vector Class Library): 
	http://www.agner.org/optimize/#vectorclass
	NOTE: For MIC support:
		a) http://www.agner.org/optimize/vectorclass.zip (download this)
		b) http://bitbucket.org/veclibknc/vclknc (MIC version by Przemysław Karpiński)
		   https://bitbucket.org/veclibknc/vclknc.git (clone this)
		=> Merge b) into a) = MIC version

